<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
Body length: 1.9-9.5 mm. Antennae longer than half or even equal to the body, segments 2 and 3 almost equal in length, segment 4 equal to or longer than sum of segments 2 and 3. Width of pronotum longer than length; anterior margin slightly depressed, basal margin protruding and lateral margins slightly protruding; basal margin and lateral margins with frame; anterior and posterior angle thickened, each angle with a seta-pore; disc convex, generally depressed on both sides. Scutellum triangular, smooth, and impunctate. Elytra broader than pronotum, humeral angle obvious; epipleuron broad before basal 1/3, then strongly narrowed and disappearing at beginning of apex. Anterior coxal cavities open or closed, each tibia with a spine in apex, spine of hind tibiae longest, 1st segment of hind tarsi longer than remaining segments combined; claws appendiculate. Last sternite of male with trilobate concavities, female normal, without any concavities (
<bibRefCitation author="Gressitt, JL" journalOrPublisher="Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" refId="B6" refString="Gressitt, JL, Kimoto, S, 1963. The Chrysomelidae (Coleopt.) of China and Korea. Part II. Pacific Insects Monograph 1B: 301-1026." title="The Chrysomelidae (Coleopt.) of China and Korea. Part II. Pacific Insects Monograph 1 B: 301 - 1026." year="1963">Gressitt and Kimoto 1963</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
Since its description, several genera have been synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authority="Chevrolat, 1837" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Monolepta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Monolepta" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Monolepta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Of these, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48423" author="Maulik, S" editor="Maulik, S [Cantab MA" journalOrPublisher="Taylor and Francis, London, Vol. 4" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="395 - 430" refId="B22" refString="Maulik, S, 1936. Coleoptera. Chrysomelidae (Galerucinae). In: Maulik, S [Cantab MA, FZS, FRES], Eds., The Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma. Taylor and Francis, London, Vol. 4: 395 - 430, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48423" title="Coleoptera. Chrysomelidae (Galerucinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.48423" volumeTitle="The Fauna of British India including Ceylon and Burma." year="1936">Maulik (1936)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName authority="Jacoby, 1903" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1903" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Damais" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Damais" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Damais</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jacoby, 1903 based on the length of the 1st segment of the hind tarsi which is longer than the remaining combined segments in 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. humeralis" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="humeralis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">D. humeralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jacoby, 1903, the type species. Konstantinov (2002) synonymized 
<taxonomicName authority="Scherer, 1969" authorityName="Scherer" authorityYear="1969" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aemulaphthona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aemulaphthona" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Aemulaphthona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Scherer, 1969, originally placed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Newman" authorityYear="1835" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="tribe" tribe="Alticini">Alticini</taxonomicName>
, based on several characters of the type species 
<taxonomicName authority="Scherer, 1969" authorityName="Scherer" authorityYear="1969" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Aemulaphthona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Aemulaphthona ochracea" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ochracea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Aemulaphthona ochracea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Weise, 1922), such as the flat head in lateral view, absence of a supraorbital sulcus, and metafemur without a metafemoral spring. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222930601127384" author="Wagner, T" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="81 - 100" refId="B31" refString="Wagner, T, 2007. Monolepta Chevrolat, 1837, the most speciose galerucine taxon: redescription of the type species Monolepta bioculata (Fabricius, 1781) and key to related genera from (Chrysomelidae, Coleoptera). Journal of Natural History 41: 81 - 100, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00222930601127384" title="Monolepta Chevrolat, 1837, the most speciose galerucine taxon: redescription of the type species Monolepta bioculata (Fabricius, 1781) and key to related genera from (Chrysomelidae, Coleoptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222930601127384" volume="41" year="2007">Wagner (2007)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName authority="Laboissière, 1931" authorityName="Laboissiere" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Chimporia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Chimporia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Chimporia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.117646" author="Laboissiere, V" journalOrPublisher="Revue Suisse de Zoologie" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="405 - 418" refId="B19" refString="Laboissiere, V, 1931. Galerucini (Coleoptera Chrysomelidae) d'Angola. Revue Suisse de Zoologie 38: 405 - 418, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.117646" title="Galerucini (Coleoptera Chrysomelidae) d'Angola." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.part.117646" volume="38" year="1931">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Laboissière">Laboissiere</normalizedToken>
1931
</bibRefCitation>
based on the similarity of the aedeagus. Also, based on characters of the anterior coxae and the second antennomere, and morphology of aedeagus, many new genera were described for species previously included in 
<taxonomicName authority="Chevrolat, 1837" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1837" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Monolepta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Monolepta" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Monolepta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, such as 
<taxonomicName authority="Hasenkamp &amp; Wagner, 2000" authorityName="Hasenkamp &amp; Wagner" authorityYear="2000" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Afromaculepta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Afromaculepta" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Afromaculepta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wagner, 2000, 
<taxonomicName authority="Schmitz &amp; Wagner, 2001" authorityName="Schmitz &amp; Wagner" authorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Afromegalepta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Afromegalepta" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Afromegalepta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wagner, 2001, 
<taxonomicName authority="Wagner &amp; Scherz, 2002" authorityName="Wagner &amp; Scherz" authorityYear="2002" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Afrocandezea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Afrocandezea" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Afrocandezea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wagner, 2002, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steiner &amp; Wagner" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Afronaumannia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Afronaumannia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Afronaumannia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wagner, 2005, 
<taxonomicName authority="Wagner, 2011" authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Monoleptoides" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Monoleptoides" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Monoleptoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wagner, 2011, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bolz &amp; Wagner, 2012" authorityName="Bolz &amp; Wagner" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Neobarombiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Neobarombiella" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Neobarombiella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Wagner, 2012, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hazmi &amp; Wagner" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Orthoneolepta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Orthoneolepta" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Orthoneolepta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hazmi &amp; Wagner, 2013, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hazmi &amp; Wagner" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Paraneolepta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Paraneolepta" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
